      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CANYA REDLINE (1) settled back off the inside but went through his gears strongly to find the frame with a 5 length third (30.11) at this track in OPEN. Expected to feature in the finish again. JUST A MENACE (2) had to overcome a collision with another runner and could manage only a distant fourth (30.50) in a OPEN over 520m at this track. Rates a key player and gets chance to atone. LIGHTNING BYTE (7) doesn't win out of turn but looks close to breaking through. Continues to race well, filling the minors at the last four starts, the latest when second (37.83) at Mandurah. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from three starts. Likely to be in the finish again. ",
